fields.description:
When using following LIC configuration for _groups_:

{code}
...
 "groups":{

    "base-dn":"ou=groups,dc=msjackson,dc=stankonia,dc=com",
    "id-attribute":"cn",
    "member-attribute":"memberUid",
    "selection":{

        "filter":"objectClass=posixGroup",
        "not-select":["cn=allusers,ou=groups,dc=msjackson,dc=stankonia,dc=com"],
    }
  },
{code}

The following warning occurs in cloud-output.log:

{code}
..
2013-04-24 13:21:36 DEBUG 001030574 LdapSync                 | Loading groups from LDAP/AD
2013-04-24 13:21:36 DEBUG 001030574 LdapSync                 | Attributes to load for groups: [cn, memberUid]
2013-04-24 13:21:36 DEBUG 001030574 LdapSync                 | Search users by: baseDn=ou=groups,dc=msjackson,dc=stankonia,dc=com, attri
butes=[Ljava.lang.String;@63827e4c, selection=filter='objectClass=posixGroup';select='[]';not-select='[cn=allusers,ou=groups,dc=msjackso
n,dc=stankonia,dc=com]'
2013-04-24 13:21:36 DEBUG 001030574 LdapSync                 | Retrieved group: cn=user01,ou=groups,dc=msjackson,dc=stankonia,dc=com ->
{memberuid=memberUid: user01, cn=cn: user01}
2013-04-24 13:21:36  WARN 001030574 LdapSync                 | Can not map member DN user01 to ID for {memberuid=memberUid: user01, cn=cn: user01}. Check corresponding selection section in your LIC.
2013-04-24 13:21:36 DEBUG 001030574 LdapSync                 | Retrieved group: cn=user02,ou=groups,dc=msjackson,dc=stankonia,dc=com -> {memberuid=memberUid: user02, cn=cn: user02}
2013-04-24 13:21:36  WARN 001030574 LdapSync                 | Can not map member DN user02 to ID for {memberuid=memberUid: user02, cn=cn: user02}. Check corresponding selection section in your LIC.
....
{code}

Per the warning, the DN being looked up is "user01" instead of the full DN (e.g. "uid=user01,ou=people,dc=msjackson,dc=stankonia,dc=com").  The group gets created under the appropriate account, but the users are not successfully synced to Eucalyptus. 

Looking at the [LdapSync.java|https://github.com/eucalyptus/eucalyptus/blob/testing/clc/modules/authentication/src/main/java/com/eucalyptus/auth/ldap/LdapSync.java#L640-L656], the following can be seen:

{code}
  private static Set<String> getMembers( String memberAttrName, Attributes attrs, final Map<String, String> dnToId ) throws NamingException {
    Set<String> members = Sets.newHashSet( );
    Attribute membersAttr = attrs.get( memberAttrName );
    if ( membersAttr != null ) {
      NamingEnumeration<?> names = membersAttr.getAll( );
      while ( names.hasMore( ) ) {
        String memberDn = ( String ) names.next( );
        String memberId = dnToId.get( memberDn.toLowerCase( ) );
        if ( Strings.isNullOrEmpty( memberId ) ) {
          LOG.warn( "Can not map member DN " + memberDn + " to ID for " + attrs + ". Check corresponding selection section in your LIC." );
        } else {
          members.add( memberId.toLowerCase( ) );
        }
      }
    }
    return members;
  }
{code}

Looks like we aren't going back to do an LDAP lookup based upon "member-attribute" to confirm the user exists.

