Hey [~mmunn1], 

No, I haven't tested it against a 3.4 cloud yet.  However, I do have a test LIC file that will confirm if the issue has been fixed or not.  Attached is atliens-euca5876.lic file.  To test with 3.4, do the following:

* After downloading the atliens-euca5876.lic file to the CLC machine, on a Eucalyptus 3.4 running cloud, add this LIC file by using the following command:
{code} 
$ euca-lictool --password password --custom atliens-euca5876.lic --out atliens-euca5876-3-4.lic --nocomment
{code}
* After that, source the admin user of the eucalyptus account creds, and enable LDAP/AD integration:
{code}
$ euca-modify-property -f authentication.ldap_integration_configuration=atliens-euca5876-3-4.lic
{code}

You should see if the sync was successful or not in /var/log/eucalyptus/cloud-output.log.

To give some background, I set up a group in the LDAP server that has membership based off of UID instead of FDN.  To view the group, make sure you are on VPN, and run the following command in the terminal (make sure you have LDAP client tools installed.  If you are running this on Mac OS X, you will be fine):
{code}
# ldapsearch -x -H ldap://10.111.5.39 -b ou=groups,dc=twodopeboyz,dc=atliens,dc=com cn=euca5876
{code}

Hope this helps.  Let me know if you have any questions.  After I set up my 3.4 cloud and if you haven't tested it yet, I will respond back to this ticket.

The option would be in the LIC, e.g. a new "member-item-type" property for groups and accounting-groups:

{code}
  "groups":{

    "base-dn":"ou=groups,dc=twodopeboyz,dc=atliens,dc=com",
    "id-attribute":"cn",
    "member-attribute":"member",
    "member-item-type":"dn" // or "identifier" 
    "selection":{
        "filter":"(&(objectClass=groupOfNames)(cn=*))",
    }
  },
{code}

The when loading the members we'd either map from DN to identifier or just use the identifier directly (after calling sanitizeUserGroupId on it) depending on the configuration option.

